<span id="freeTextContainer6760908373270675903">I was one of the beta readers of this book, reading it chapter by chapter as it was written. I liked it a lot when I was reading it, but there were a few holes in the plot. Grahame fixed all of them and added some flashbacks to give insight into the characters.<br/><br/>The first draft was rather short on violence. I suggested he could destroy a few things like planes and ships, since being fiction, he wouldn&apos;t have to pay for them. He did that and I&apos;m happy now, as long as he doesn&apos;t crash the Alfa-Romeo</span>
  <span id="freeText6760908373270675903" style="display:none">I was one of the beta readers of this book, reading it chapter by chapter as it was written. I liked it a lot when I was reading it, but there were a few holes in the plot. Grahame fixed all of them and added some flashbacks to give insight into the characters.<br /><br />The first draft was rather short on violence. I suggested he could destroy a few things like planes and ships, since being fiction, he wouldn't have to pay for them. He did that and I'm happy now, as long as he doesn't crash the Alfa-Romeo.<br /><br />A fun read with all the elements of a successful mystery-thriller.</span>
